{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"77609e14-56cb-4e93-8a4f-4052950a4359","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nIf you need to specify the project:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so `FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests` matches any test whose fully qualified name includes that string. Use `=` for exact matches on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2c4736bb-353c-4ca0-a988-e1591b356127","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":195,"requestId":"7695:1C19C7:895EC:A196C:69F2AEAC"},"id":"1b2603f6-0df1-4363-b20f-109ee0aced99","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:21:53.209Z","parentId":"52e748dc-d9bb-4d63-9572-88cda9a1b0b6"}
